article.headline: Georgetown 104, North Carolina 72
article.story: CHAPEL HILL, N.C. (AP) -- Sean May had 22 points and 16 rebounds, and No. 9 North Carolina beat Team Nike 104-72 in exhibition game Thursday night. May went 9-for-14 from the field and made all four of his free throws in the Tar Heels' final tuneup before their season opener Nov. 22 at home against Old Dominion. Jawad Williams also scored 22 points and Rashad McCants added 15 as North Carolina shot 53 percent, including 47 percent from 3-point range. The Tar Heels trailed 29-26 late in the first half before scoring 11 straight points, helped by a pair of jump shots from Raymond Felton. Brandon Watkins led Team Nike with 21 points.
